<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>This if statement in partialLoop() evaluates to true when given an empty array. This should not be the case, as exceptions will be thrown when module name is given.</p>

<p>Starts on line 57:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if ((null == $model) &amp;&amp; (null !== $module)) {
    $model  = $module;
    $module = null;
} 
</code></pre>

<p>Should read:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if ((null === $model) &amp;&amp; (null !== $module)) {
    $model  = $module;
    $module = null;
} 
</code></pre>

<p>Notice the triple ===.</p>

